%N A365482 In the Collatz (3x+1) problem, values in A006884 for which the maximum excursion ratio (see comments) is greater than 2.
%C A365482 Kontorovich and Lagarias (2009, 2010) define the maximum excursion ratio as the ratio between the log of the highest point in the trajectory of the T function (started at x) and the log of x, where T(x) is the 3x+1 function = (3x+1)/2 if x is odd, x/2 if x is even (A014682).
%C A365482 They use data from Oliveira e Silva (2010) to compile Table 3 in their paper, but they omit the a(7) = 10709980568908647 value (cf. also Barina and Roosendall links).
%C A365482 Equivalently, values in A006884 for which A365478(A006884(k)) / A006884(k)^2 > 1, for k >= 1.
%C A365482 See A365483 for corresponding maximum excursion values.
